                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/882a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-02T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 2, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Please ascertain whether British Government is pursuing endeavors to obtain
                    definite information on Japanese naval plans and, if so, whether they have any
                    hope of obtaining an early decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
